# 9. Palindrome Number

##Approach
Negative numbers and numbers ending with 0 (except 0 itself) cannot be palindromes.
Reverse only half of the number instead of the entire number.
Stop when the reversed half becomes greater than or equal to the remaining half.
For even digits, compare both halves directly.
For odd digits, ignore the middle digit by dividing the reversed half by 10 before comparing.
Time Complexity

O(log₁₀ n)

Space Complexity

O(1)

##Code : 

class Solution {
    public boolean isPalindrome(int x) {
        if (x < 0 || (x % 10 == 0 && x != 0)) {
            return false;
        }

        int reversedHalf = 0;

        while (x > reversedHalf) {
            reversedHalf = reversedHalf * 10 + x % 10;
            x /= 10;
        }

        return x == reversedHalf || x == reversedHalf / 10;
    }
}
